name: MicroserviceJobApplication
description: A microservice application that handles the job applications and reviews from various organizations enlisted on the platform, built with JAVA 21 and Spring boot 3

name: Microservices-Shopping-Application
description: Three Stage Project for the course Cloud Computing. Title: Migrating a monolithic e-commerce application to a microservices architecture

name: movie-application
description: This is a movie application built using Microservices architecture to create a API where you can register categories, genres, cast members, and movies

name: quiz_microservice
description: This project is a Quiz application built using Spring Boot 3 and Spring Cloud. It leverages microservices architecture to ensure scalability and maintainability. The application uses Hibernate JPA for database interactions with MySQL and includes an API Gateway for routing and managing API requests.

name: Blog-Microservices
description: This is my first time building a microservices application. I focused on the communication between services and their deployment.

name: sam-app
description: Using AWS Serverless Application Model (SAM) to deploy a microservice

name: resilient-services
description: Banking simulation application built with microservices architecture, including resiliency, containerization, orchestration and more

name: E-Commerce_ProductService
description: This repository hosts a Java-based e-commerce application using a microservices architecture. Each microservice handles distinct functionalities, ensuring scalability and independent deployment.

name: header-parser
description: Build a full stack JavaScript application that parses and displays client request headers, similar to the FreeCodeCamp Request Header Parser Microservice project.

name: GPS-Violation-Detection
description: In this project, we created a web application using microservices to reduce car theft and allow users to track and monitor their cars.

description: Multi-user application consisting of 4 microservices working together that allows users to create accounts and save, prioritize, and schedule tasks in a to-do list

description: A Go-based application designed to handle file uploads, process XML data, and store the processed data in a MongoDB database. This microservice uses Gorilla Mux for routing.

name: port-service
description: Go-based microservices application. It demonstrates proficiency in hexagonal architecture, gRPC, Domain-Driven Design (DDD), and various streaming and data persistence techniques. The application provides two key adapter implementations: a gRPC streaming API and filesystem-based data streaming.

name: webapp
description: This project develops a cloud native web app using Java Spring Boot and MySQL, following a microservices architecture. Custom application images are created with Packer for deployment on Google Cloud Platform (GCP), ensuring they include all necessary dependencies.
